WEBVTT

00:12.000 --> 00:14.166
JUST GOT OFF WITH NBC.
GUESS WHAT.

00:14.166 --> 00:15.458
You don't have
to audition.

00:15.458 --> 00:16.375
NO SHIT?

00:16.375 --> 00:17.750
YOU JUST HAVE
TO GO IN AND MEET.

00:17.750 --> 00:18.875
AND I DON'T HAVE TO READ?

00:18.875 --> 00:21.041
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO READ.
All right.

00:21.041 --> 00:23.333
I'M THINKING IT'S TIME
TO STOP TAKING THE MEDS.

00:23.333 --> 00:26.500
IT WOULD BE A HUGE MISTAKE
TO STOP NOW.

00:26.500 --> 00:27.959
I CANNOT STRESS THIS ENOUGH.

00:30.792 --> 00:31.709
AAH!

00:31.709 --> 00:33.709
THIS SCRIPT ISN'T GOING TO YOU.

00:33.709 --> 00:35.709
IT ISN'T GOING TO FOX.

00:35.709 --> 00:38.583
THE ONLY PLACE IT'S GOING
IS IN OUR SUITCASE HOME.

00:38.583 --> 00:39.709
OKAY.

00:39.709 --> 00:42.542
YOU DON'T PURSUE IT
BEHIND OUR BACKS.

00:42.542 --> 00:44.250
IT'S OVER.

00:44.250 --> 00:45.750
OH, MY GOD.

00:45.750 --> 00:47.375
THIS ONE FOUND A WINNER.

00:47.375 --> 00:48.375
I READ IT LAST NIGHT.

00:48.375 --> 00:49.709
I DON'T WANT
TO EVEN SHOOT A PILOT.

00:49.709 --> 00:51.792
I WANT TO GO
STRAIGHT TO SERIES.

00:51.792 --> 00:53.083
HOW SOON CAN THEY START?

00:55.375 --> 00:58.083
[ TYPEWRITER CLICKING,
BELL CHIMES ]

01:01.291 --> 01:03.166
[ WIND WHISTLING ]

01:08.750 --> 01:11.250
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

01:35.959 --> 01:38.041
[ GUNSHOT ]

01:47.542 --> 01:49.542
Carol: HEY, KIDS.

01:49.542 --> 01:50.750
HELLO.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.083
THIS IS A NICE SURPRISE.

01:52.083 --> 01:55.583
SO, THIS IS
WHERE THE MAGIC HAPPENS.

01:55.583 --> 01:56.875
HAPPENED.

01:56.875 --> 01:58.709
[ LAUGHS ] RIGHT.

01:58.709 --> 02:00.583
APPARENTLY, NOBODY
WANTED TO SEE OUR TRICKS.

02:00.583 --> 02:01.750
[ LAUGHS ]

02:01.750 --> 02:05.625
ANYWAY,
WHILE I'VE GOT YOU --

02:05.625 --> 02:07.125
AND DON'T BITE
MY HEAD OFF...

02:07.125 --> 02:09.625
THIS BETTER NOT BE GOING
WHERE I THINK IT'S GOING.

02:09.625 --> 02:11.583
I JUST WANT TO HAVE
A CONVERSATION.

02:11.583 --> 02:12.583
RIGHT.

02:12.583 --> 02:14.458
AND WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE CONVERSATION

02:14.458 --> 02:17.750
WHERE WE AGREED WE WOULD NEVER,
EVER HAVE THIS CONVERSATION?

02:17.750 --> 02:21.417
THAT WAS BEFORE CASTOR
SAW YOUR SCRIPT.

02:21.417 --> 02:24.542
OH.
HE "SAW" IT!

02:24.542 --> 02:27.000
[ High-pitched voice ] I SWEAR!
I DIDN'T SHOW IT TO HIM!

02:27.000 --> 02:29.041
THAT'S THE OCTAVE
YOU USUALLY LIE IN.

02:29.041 --> 02:30.125
[ Normal voice ] HONEST.

02:30.125 --> 02:32.208
HE WAS SNOOPING
AROUND MY DESK.

02:32.208 --> 02:35.291
HE SAW IT AND READ IT,
AND -- HELLO! --

02:35.291 --> 02:36.625
HE LOVED IT.

02:36.625 --> 02:37.625
REALLY?

02:37.625 --> 02:39.250
LOVED  IT.

02:39.250 --> 02:41.125
OF ALL THE THINGS
I'VE SHOWN HIM,

02:41.125 --> 02:43.166
IT'S THE ONLY ONE
HE WANTS TO DO.

02:43.166 --> 02:44.667
SO YOU DID  SHOW IT TO HIM.
OH, SO WHAT?

02:44.667 --> 02:46.458
[ SIGHS ]

02:46.458 --> 02:48.083
I HAD TO!

02:48.083 --> 02:50.041
MY JOB IS ON THE LINE!

02:50.041 --> 02:51.583
HE HATES EVERYTHING.

02:51.583 --> 02:52.917
YOUR THING?

02:52.917 --> 02:54.667
HE DOESN'T EVEN WANT
TO SHOOT A PILOT.

02:54.667 --> 02:56.667
HE WANTS TO GO
STRAIGHT TO SERIES.

02:56.667 --> 02:58.709
I LIKE THE SOUND OF THAT.
I DON'T.

02:58.709 --> 03:00.500
THAT JUST MEANS
WE GET TO SKIP LIMBO

03:00.500 --> 03:02.166
AND GO STRAIGHT TO HELL.

03:02.166 --> 03:03.375
OKAY.
HOW ABOUT THIS?

03:03.375 --> 03:06.000
WHAT IF WE JUST BUY
THE SHOW FROM YOU?

03:06.000 --> 03:07.959
WE'LL HIRE SOMEONE ELSE
TO RUN IT.

03:07.959 --> 03:09.667
YOU WON'T EVEN
HAVE TO BE HERE.

03:09.667 --> 03:11.125
NO. NO, NO.
IT'S OUR SHOW.

03:11.125 --> 03:12.959
IF ANYONE'S GONNA RUN IT,
IT'LL BE US.

03:12.959 --> 03:14.834
WELL, YOU KNOW
I'D LOVE THAT.

03:14.834 --> 03:16.000
FORGET IT!

03:16.000 --> 03:18.250
WE'RE GOING HOME.

03:18.250 --> 03:20.000
TO DO WHAT?

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WHEN YOU GET THERE?

03:22.000 --> 03:23.625
TRY TO GET ANOTHER SHOW ON?

03:23.625 --> 03:27.166
AND EVEN IF YOU DO,
YOU'LL MAKE, WHAT, SIX EPISODES

03:27.166 --> 03:29.291
OF SOMETHING
NO ONE WILL EVER SEE?

03:29.291 --> 03:30.500
WELL, ENGLAND.

03:30.500 --> 03:31.709
EXACTLY.

03:31.709 --> 03:33.083
SO, ARE JUST SUPPOSED

03:33.083 --> 03:35.166
TO IGNORE THE DISASTER
OF THE LAST 10 MONTHS?

03:35.166 --> 03:38.375
WE FINALLY GOT OUT
OF THIS ONE.

03:38.375 --> 03:40.917
I AM NOT GOING BACK
INTO THE BURNING BUILDING.

03:40.917 --> 03:42.542
I DON'T CARE.

03:42.542 --> 03:46.166
LET THE FUCKING CAT DIE.

03:55.709 --> 03:56.625
WHERE ARE YOU?

03:56.625 --> 03:59.333
I DON'T KNOW.

04:03.125 --> 04:05.500
MAYBE IT COULD BE DIFFERENT
WITH A DIFFERENT SHOW.

04:05.500 --> 04:09.500
MM.

04:09.500 --> 04:12.500
I THINK IT'S LIKE TOSSING
THOSE RINGS AT THE FUN FAIR.

04:12.500 --> 04:15.583
EACH TIME, YOU'RE SO SURE
YOU'LL GET IT.

04:15.583 --> 04:16.959
RIGHT.

04:16.959 --> 04:18.417
BUT, BELIEVE ME,

04:18.417 --> 04:23.083
YOU'RE NOT GONNA WALK AWAY
WITH A STUFFED GIRAFFE HERE.

04:23.083 --> 04:25.417
YOU JUST HAVE TO WALK AWAY.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.208
I WANT A GIRAFFE.

04:29.208 --> 04:31.250
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:32.625 --> 04:33.792
I KNOW YOU DO.

04:33.792 --> 04:37.875
AND IN THIS TOWN,
IF YOU CAN  WIN A GIRAFFE...

04:37.875 --> 04:44.375
RIGHT,
BUT [SIGHS] THIS TOWN --

04:44.375 --> 04:46.166
IT'S NO GOOD FOR US.

04:46.166 --> 04:47.917
IT NEARLY DID US IN.

04:47.917 --> 04:50.083
THAT IS TRUE.

04:51.417 --> 04:55.291
WE'VE WORKED SO HARD
TO GET BACK TO A GOOD PLACE.

04:57.041 --> 04:59.083
AND IT'S A VERY GOOD PLACE.

05:07.208 --> 05:09.750
WE DO SO MUCH BETTER
AT HOME.

05:12.458 --> 05:13.583
I AGREE.

05:13.583 --> 05:16.458
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:16.458 --> 05:18.500
THANK YOU.

05:23.000 --> 05:25.750
MMM.

05:25.750 --> 05:27.834
IS THAT A GIRAFFE?

05:27.834 --> 05:30.333
IT JUST MAY BE.

05:30.333 --> 05:33.000
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:37.250 --> 05:38.750
I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO GET YOU.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.417
OH, SHOOT.
MY PHONE WAS OFF.

05:40.417 --> 05:41.500
WHY?

05:41.500 --> 05:43.458
I WAS GETTING WAXED.

05:43.458 --> 05:46.542
IF IT RINGS, IT STARTLES HER,
AND THEN -- BLGGGH!

05:46.542 --> 05:47.458
WHAT'S GOING ON?

05:47.458 --> 05:48.834
CASTOR CALLED
A BIG MEETING.

05:48.834 --> 05:49.875
FOR WHEN?
20 MINUTES AGO.

05:49.875 --> 05:51.000
WHAT?!

05:51.000 --> 05:52.000
IT WAS TOTALLY
LAST MINUTE.

05:52.000 --> 05:53.166
EVERYONE'S ALREADY IN THERE,
EVEN ELLIOT.

05:53.166 --> 05:54.000
ELLIOT'S HERE?!
MM-HMM.

05:54.000 --> 05:56.917
JESUS CHRIST!

05:56.917 --> 05:58.166
BUT IT'S NOT JUST US.

05:58.166 --> 06:02.208
ALL NETWORK TV IS --

06:02.208 --> 06:05.041
[ CHUCKLES ] So Sorry.

06:05.041 --> 06:06.834
I didn't know.

06:06.834 --> 06:08.458
Keep going.

06:10.166 --> 06:12.291
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

06:20.792 --> 06:20.834
[ BOOK THUDS ]

06:24.583 --> 06:26.542
WHERE WAS I?

06:26.542 --> 06:27.792
UH,
"ALL NETWORK TV IS..."

06:27.792 --> 06:28.792
RIGHT.

06:28.792 --> 06:30.875
...DYING.

06:30.875 --> 06:34.917
NETWORK TV IS DYING.

06:34.917 --> 06:38.834
EVERY YEAR,
OUR RATINGS GET LOWER.

06:38.834 --> 06:40.208
CABLE IS KILLING US.

06:40.208 --> 06:42.709
THE INTERNET IS KILLING US.

06:42.709 --> 06:46.000
WE'RE CANCELING SHOWS
AT AN UNPRECEDENTED RATE.

06:46.000 --> 06:48.208
AND WHAT DO WE DO?

06:48.208 --> 06:50.166
WE SIT AROUND
WITH OUR HEADS UP OUR ASSES

06:50.166 --> 06:51.291
SAYING,
"I DON'T SMELL ANYTHING.

06:51.291 --> 06:52.709
DO YOU?"

06:52.709 --> 06:56.250
WE PUT OUT A PRODUCT
THAT'S PREDICTABLE AND STALE,

06:56.250 --> 06:59.291
AND WE WONDER
WHY NO ONE'S WATCHING.

06:59.291 --> 07:00.917
SO NOW THAT YOU'VE DEPRESSED
THE SHIT OUT OF US,

07:00.917 --> 07:02.083
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

07:02.083 --> 07:05.083
OKAY. WE NEED TO LOOK
AT THE BIG PICTURE.

07:05.083 --> 07:08.625
WE NEED TO MAKE BOLD MOVES,
CHANGE THE PARADIGM.

07:09.542 --> 07:11.333
WHAT'S THE HOTTEST THING
RIGHT NOW?

07:11.333 --> 07:12.959
KARDASHIANS.
ZOMBIES!

07:12.959 --> 07:14.291
CLOSE.

07:14.291 --> 07:16.834
WHY ARE WE SO OBSESSED
WITH ZOMBIES?

07:16.834 --> 07:18.417
THEY'RE SCARY.

07:18.417 --> 07:20.166
RIGHT! WHY?

07:20.166 --> 07:21.583
'CAUSE THEY'RE ZOMBIES?

07:21.583 --> 07:23.458
THEY'RE SCARY
'CAUSE THEY'RE UNPREDICTABLE!

07:23.458 --> 07:24.500
YES!

07:24.500 --> 07:25.583
YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN
THEY'RE GOING TO ATTACK.

07:25.583 --> 07:26.500
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.

07:26.500 --> 07:28.041
YOU WANT TO DO
A ZOMBIE SHOW?

07:28.041 --> 07:29.458
YOU KNOW,
THERE ARE ACTUALLY

07:29.458 --> 07:31.959
A COUPLE OF REALLY STRONG
ZOMBIE SCRIPTS.

07:31.959 --> 07:35.583
NO! CHRIST!
I'M NOT SAYING WE DO  ZOMBIES.

07:35.583 --> 07:39.834
I'M SAYING WE BECOME  ZOMBIES.

07:41.208 --> 07:42.625
ALL RIGHTY. [ CHUCKLES ]

07:42.625 --> 07:45.291
WE NEED TO BE UNEXPECTED,
STARTLING, DANGEROUS!

07:45.291 --> 07:47.583
AND HOW DO YOU PROPOSE
WE DO THAT?

07:47.583 --> 07:48.500
ALL RIGHT.

07:48.500 --> 07:53.417
START BY THROWING AWAY
THE "WHEN."

07:54.583 --> 07:56.458
"WHEN'S THE SHOW ON?"
DOESN'T MATTER.

07:56.458 --> 07:58.458
WE'RE LIVING IN A WORLD
WHERE YOUR TV

07:58.458 --> 08:00.458
IS BECOMING YOUR COMPUTER
IS BECOMING YOUR iPAD

08:00.458 --> 08:01.583
IS BECOMING YOUR PHONE.

08:01.583 --> 08:04.542
WHEN THE SHOW'S ON
IS IRRELEVANT.

08:04.542 --> 08:07.041
YOU DON'T GO,
"WHEN'S THAT YouTube VIDEO ON?"

08:07.041 --> 08:09.125
IT'S JUST ON.

08:09.125 --> 08:11.875
SO, FORGET THE WHEN.

08:11.875 --> 08:18.417
FORGET "NIGHTS" AND "TIME SLOTS"
AND "LEAD-INS."

08:18.417 --> 08:21.250
SO, HOW ARE PEOPLE
SUPPOSED TO KNOW WHEN --

08:21.250 --> 08:22.500
FORGET THE WHEN!

08:22.500 --> 08:24.667
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
WHAT -- WHAT WHEN?

08:24.667 --> 08:30.083
WHAT I MEAN IS,
HOW WILL THEY KNOW WHAT'S ON?

08:30.083 --> 08:32.083
THEY WON'T.

08:32.083 --> 08:34.208
THAT'S THE BEAUTY!

08:34.208 --> 08:38.250
WE'VE GOT TO ESCAPE
THE TYRANNY OF THE SCHEDULE.

08:38.250 --> 08:40.458
GET RID OF ALL OF IT!

08:43.542 --> 08:45.125
[ GRUNTING ]

08:47.875 --> 08:49.125
JESUS.

08:49.125 --> 08:50.583
DIDN'T SEE THAT COMING.

08:50.583 --> 08:54.458
FROM NOW ON,
WE PROGRAM ANYTHING AT ANY TIME.

08:54.458 --> 08:57.000
COMEDY, DRAMA, REALITY --
MIX IT THE FUCK UP.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.250
MAYBE ONE NIGHT,
FOUR HOURS ALL ABOUT BEES!

09:00.250 --> 09:01.667
BEES?
BEES!

09:01.667 --> 09:02.834
THE NEXT DAY,
PEOPLE WILL BE ALL,

09:02.834 --> 09:04.458
"DID YOU SEE THAT FUCKING THING
ABOUT THE BEES?"

09:04.458 --> 09:06.208
THE SHEER BALLS OF IT!

09:06.208 --> 09:07.375
UH, HELP ME OUT HERE.

09:07.375 --> 09:09.041
WHAT ARE THE BEES DOING?

09:09.041 --> 09:10.834
ARE THEY FUNNY BEES?

09:10.834 --> 09:12.667
ARE THEY KILLER BEES?

09:12.667 --> 09:14.583
DO THEY HAVE A TALENT?

09:14.583 --> 09:15.792
I DON'T KNOW. WHO GIVES A SHIT?
THEY'RE BEES.

09:15.792 --> 09:16.834
THEY'LL DO WHATEVER BEES DO.

09:16.834 --> 09:17.709
THE POINT IS,

09:17.709 --> 09:19.250
PEOPLE ARE GONNA TUNE IN
TO FIND OUT

09:19.250 --> 09:20.208
WHAT THE HELL WE'RE DOING NEXT.

09:20.208 --> 09:22.291
IT'S TOTAL WATER COOLER.

09:22.291 --> 09:24.875
OH! AND EVERYTHING'S LIVE.

09:24.875 --> 09:25.959
THE BEES ARE LIVE?

09:25.959 --> 09:27.917
MAYBE!
HOW FUCKING GREAT WOULD THAT BE?

09:27.917 --> 09:28.875
[ WHIMPERS ]

09:28.875 --> 09:30.917
PEOPLE,
WE GOT TO THROW AWAY THE RULES.

09:30.917 --> 09:33.208
LIKE, WHO SAYS
ONE SHOW HAS TO END

09:33.208 --> 09:34.792
BEFORE ANOTHER ONE CAN START?

09:34.792 --> 09:36.542
HOW DO YOU -- WAIT.
WHAT NOW?

09:36.542 --> 09:37.458
OKAY, SAY YOU'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOME COOKING SHOW.

09:37.458 --> 09:38.834
THIS WOMAN'S COOKING
AND COOKING,

09:38.834 --> 09:39.750
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,

09:39.750 --> 09:41.625
THE BAD GUY
FROM ONE OF OUR DRAMAS

09:41.625 --> 09:44.291
RUNS IN WITH A FUCKING GUN
AND HOLDS HER FUCKING HOSTAGE!

09:44.291 --> 09:46.750
MEANWHILE, SHE HAS NO IDEA
WHAT THE FUCK IS HAPPENING!

09:46.750 --> 09:48.750
THE ACTUAL WOMAN FROM
THE COOKING SHOW DOESN'T KNOW?

09:48.750 --> 09:50.583
RIGHT! SHE'S LIKE, "AAH!
WHAT THE FUCK IS HAPPENING?!"

09:50.583 --> 09:52.208
AND PEOPLE ARE TWEETING
AND TWITTERING --

09:52.208 --> 09:54.125
"YOU GOT TO WATCH THIS!
TURN IT ON! TURN IT ON!"

09:54.125 --> 09:55.917
THEN, ONE OF THE COPS
FROM THE DRAMA

09:55.917 --> 09:58.041
RUNS IN AND SHOOTS HIM --
I MEAN, ACTUALLY SHOOTS HIM.

09:58.041 --> 09:59.750
WE'RE SHOOTING
ONE OF OUR ACTORS?

09:59.750 --> 10:00.834
SO WE'LL HAVE TO PAY HIM MORE.

10:00.834 --> 10:02.375
YOU KNOW THERE ARE ACTORS
WHO WILL DO IT.

10:02.375 --> 10:04.583
SO WE SHOOT HIM,
THEN THE POLICE RUN IN --

10:04.583 --> 10:06.583
THE REAL POLICE --
AND IT'S NEWS.

10:06.583 --> 10:08.583
THEN WE CUT TO OUR NEWS GUY.

10:08.583 --> 10:10.500
THAT'S WHEN
OUR NEWS SHOW STARTS.

10:10.500 --> 10:14.041
WE MAKE THE NEWS,
THEN WE REPORT THE NEWS,

10:14.041 --> 10:15.834
AND NO ONE'S GONNA
REPORT IT BEFORE US

10:15.834 --> 10:18.333
BECAUSE WE'RE THE ONLY ONES
WHO KNOW WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

10:18.333 --> 10:21.083
IT'S TV FOR A NEW CENTURY.

10:21.083 --> 10:24.709
AND THAT'S WHY THEY'RE GONNA
WATCH US AND NOT THE OTHER GUYS.

10:25.667 --> 10:28.458
HOW ABOUT THAT, MY ZOMBIES?!

10:28.458 --> 10:30.917
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

10:45.083 --> 10:46.333
SO HE WAS CRAZY.

10:46.333 --> 10:47.959
YEAH.

10:51.458 --> 10:53.834
HEY, MATT.

10:53.834 --> 10:55.125
BERTA NISSICK.

10:55.125 --> 10:56.458
HI.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:56.458 --> 10:58.375
ACTUALLY,
WE'VE MET BEFORE.

10:58.375 --> 11:00.417
I WAS THE JUNIOR JUNIOR
CASTING PERSON

11:00.417 --> 11:01.750
ON "MARRIED WITH CHILDREN."

11:01.750 --> 11:02.875
OH, WOW.

11:02.875 --> 11:04.375
OH, YOU PROBABLY
DON'T REMEMBER,

11:04.375 --> 11:06.125
BUT YOU HIT ON ME
AT THE WRAP PARTY.

11:06.125 --> 11:07.125
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:07.125 --> 11:09.250
OKAY.

11:09.250 --> 11:10.375
SO, THIS SHOULD BE FUN.

11:10.375 --> 11:11.542
I'M GONNA READ WITH YOU.

11:11.542 --> 11:13.166
SO IF THERE'S ANYTHING

11:13.166 --> 11:14.875
YOU WANT ME TO DO
OR DON'T WANT ME TO DO...

11:14.875 --> 11:16.125
WAIT. WHAT?
WHAT?

11:16.125 --> 11:18.542
UH [CHUCKLES]
I'M NOT READING.

11:18.542 --> 11:19.500
WHAT?

11:19.500 --> 11:21.667
NO, MY AGENT
SPOKE TO SOMEONE,

11:21.667 --> 11:24.750
AND IT WAS ABSOLUTELY UNDERSTOOD
THAT IT'S JUST A MEETING.

11:24.750 --> 11:26.083
AH.

11:26.083 --> 11:27.125
UM...

11:27.125 --> 11:30.500
WELL, THAT'S NOT
THE INFORMATION WE GOT.

11:30.500 --> 11:31.625
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:31.625 --> 11:33.000
ANDREW AND THE EXECS
ARE IN THERE,

11:33.000 --> 11:34.000
WAITING FOR YOU TO READ.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.375
WELL,
THAT'S NOT HAPPENING.

11:36.375 --> 11:38.250
OKAY.

11:38.250 --> 11:39.834
UM, JUST GIVE ME A SEC.

11:39.834 --> 11:41.375
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
YEAH, WHATEVER.

11:41.375 --> 11:42.792
YEAH,
I'M CALLING MY AGENT.

11:42.792 --> 11:44.208
GOOD.
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

11:44.208 --> 11:45.166
OKAY.
GOOD.

11:45.166 --> 11:46.333
[ Chuckling ] YEAH.

11:49.542 --> 11:52.375
HEY, IT'S MATT LeBLANC.
IS HE THERE?

11:52.375 --> 11:54.208
CAN YOU REACH HIM?

11:54.208 --> 11:56.625
NO, NO. I NEED HIM NOW.

11:56.625 --> 11:57.750
'CAUSE I'M AT FUCKING NBC,

11:57.750 --> 11:59.583
ABOUT TO GO
INTO A FUCKING MEETING,

11:59.583 --> 12:01.208
AND THEY THINK
I'M FUCKING READING,

12:01.208 --> 12:02.333
WHICH I AM FUCKING NOT!

12:02.333 --> 12:04.417
LISTEN, AS SOON
AS YOU HEAR FROM HIM,

12:04.417 --> 12:06.333
YOU HAVE HIM CALL ME ON MY CELL.

12:08.375 --> 12:13.125
MONSIEUR LeBLANC,
WHAT A CLUSTERFUCK.

12:13.125 --> 12:15.500
WE WERE TOLD
YOU WERE GOING TO READ.

12:15.500 --> 12:18.333
NO. THE WHOLE DEAL WAS
I'M NOT GONNA READ.

12:18.333 --> 12:20.417
BUT THEN WE HEARD
THAT YOU WERE.

12:20.417 --> 12:21.583
NO.
[ SCOFFS ]

12:21.583 --> 12:23.458
HOW DOES THIS HAPPEN?
I DON'T KNOW.

12:23.458 --> 12:26.000
IT'S MORTIFYING.
I AM MORTIFIED.

12:26.000 --> 12:27.000
I AGREE.

12:27.000 --> 12:28.375
[ SIGHS ]

12:28.375 --> 12:29.625
SO, WHAT DO WE DO?

12:29.625 --> 12:31.917
I DON'T KNOW.
THEY'RE WAITING.

12:31.917 --> 12:33.458
YOU KNOW,
IF IT WERE JUST UP TO ME,

12:33.458 --> 12:35.625
I WOULD GIVE YOU THE PART
IN A HEARTBEAT,

12:35.625 --> 12:37.250
BUT IT'S
THE FUCKING SUITS.

12:37.250 --> 12:38.959
IT'S BECOMING
A PISSING MATCH.

12:38.959 --> 12:41.542
OKAY, LOOK, YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
I LOVE THIS THING.

12:41.542 --> 12:43.917
BUT, NO,
I'M NOT READING.

12:45.917 --> 12:47.417
IN ALL FAIRNESS --

12:47.417 --> 12:49.375
AND I PROBABLY
SHOULDN'T TELL YOU THIS --

12:49.375 --> 12:52.417
THERE IS ANOTHER ACTOR
THEY'RE VERY KEEN ON.

12:52.417 --> 12:53.417
WHO?

12:53.417 --> 12:54.917
I CAN'T SAY.

12:54.917 --> 12:55.917
CAN I?
NO.

12:55.917 --> 12:56.959
NO?
NO.

12:56.959 --> 12:59.417
HE CAME IN YESTERDAY,

12:59.417 --> 13:02.083
AND HE WAS FINE IN A TOTALLY
BORING WAY YOU'D EXPECT

13:02.083 --> 13:04.041
IF YOU KNEW
WHO I WAS TALKING ABOUT.

13:04.041 --> 13:05.917
[ IMITATES SNORING ]
[ LAUGHS ]

13:05.917 --> 13:07.417
BUT IF YOU DON'T
READ TODAY,

13:07.417 --> 13:09.166
THEY'RE GONNA GIVE THE PART
TO HIM.

13:09.166 --> 13:11.375
PLUS, HE'S A LOT CHEAPER
THAN YOU.

13:11.375 --> 13:12.542
A lot.

13:12.542 --> 13:13.917
PLEASE.

13:13.917 --> 13:15.625
I BESEECH YOU.

13:15.625 --> 13:18.917
[ SIGHS ]

13:23.542 --> 13:25.125
NO.

13:25.125 --> 13:26.250
NO.

13:26.250 --> 13:27.625
I'M NOT GONNA EAT
THEIR SHIT.

13:27.625 --> 13:29.000
OH, COME ON!

13:29.000 --> 13:31.125
WE ALL HAVE TO EAT SHIT
NOW AND THEN.

13:31.125 --> 13:33.583
YOU JUST HAVE TO EAT IT
UNTIL THE SHOW'S A BIG HIT --

13:33.583 --> 13:34.792
THEN THEY'LL
HAVE TO EAT YOURS.

13:34.792 --> 13:37.333
IT'S CALLED
"SHOW BUSINESS."

13:37.333 --> 13:39.917
NO. I'M SORRY.

13:39.917 --> 13:42.166
GOOD LUCK
WITH THE PROJECT.

13:46.417 --> 13:48.709
SO YOU JUST WALKED OUT?

13:48.709 --> 13:49.792
HEY, AT A CERTAIN POINT,

13:49.792 --> 13:51.875
SOMEONE HAS TO SAY NO
TO THESE ASSHOLES.

13:51.875 --> 13:55.250
IT'S A VERY STRANGE DAY
WHEN YOU'RE MY HERO.
AWW.

13:55.250 --> 13:57.208
SO, DO WE KNOW WHO THE OTHER
GUY IS WHO'S GETTING THE PART?

13:57.208 --> 13:58.250
NAH.

13:58.250 --> 13:59.500
THEY WERE JUST USING THAT
TO GET ME TO READ.

13:59.500 --> 14:01.375
THERE PROBABLY
ISN'T EVEN ANOTHER GUY.

14:01.375 --> 14:02.583
REALLY?

14:02.583 --> 14:03.834
HERE'S WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

14:03.834 --> 14:05.750
RIGHT NOW,
THEY'RE TELLING EACH OTHER

14:05.750 --> 14:07.583
THEY DIDN'T WANT ME
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

14:07.583 --> 14:11.917
THEN THEY'LL OFFER IT TO SOME
BIG MOVIE GUY LIKE NICOLAS CAGE,

14:11.917 --> 14:14.834
WHO YOU KNOW
ISN'T GONNA DO TV,

14:14.834 --> 14:16.125
BUT HE'LL JERK THEM AROUND
FOR A WHILE,

14:16.125 --> 14:19.083
THEN COME BACK AND SAY
[GASPS] HE WON'T DO TV.

14:19.083 --> 14:20.542
THEN THEY'LL GO TO, LIKE,

14:20.542 --> 14:23.667
SOME BIG BROADWAY STAR
WHO NOBODY'S FUCKING HEARD OF,

14:23.667 --> 14:25.458
AND HE WON'T WANT
TO LEAVE NEW YORK,

14:25.458 --> 14:27.208
WHICH ONLY MAKES THEM
WANT HIM MORE.

14:27.208 --> 14:29.250
SO THEY'LL OFFER
TO SHOOT IT IN NEW YORK,

14:29.250 --> 14:31.208
BUT THEN THE BROADWAY GUY
WILL DECIDE

14:31.208 --> 14:32.375
HE DOESN'T WANT TO DO TV.

14:32.375 --> 14:34.750
THEN THEY'LL JUST GIVE IT
TO DYLAN McDERMOTT.

14:34.750 --> 14:37.208
AND THAT'S WHY
I WANT TO GO HOME.

14:37.208 --> 14:39.417
RIGHT. BUT IN THE MEANTIME,
YOU'RE HERE.

14:39.417 --> 14:43.542
SO...TO THE THREE OF US
IN WHAT WAS, ON THE WHOLE,

14:43.542 --> 14:45.208
A FAIRLY SHITTY
EXPERIENCE...
[ LAUGHS ]

14:45.208 --> 14:46.458
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
SORRY.

14:46.458 --> 14:48.083
HOLD THAT THOUGHT.

14:48.083 --> 14:49.583
YOU WERE UP
TO "SHITTY EXPERIENCE."

14:49.583 --> 14:50.542
HELLO?

14:50.542 --> 14:53.208
SEAN, HI. IT'S EILEEN.

14:53.208 --> 14:57.959
DID CAROL RANCE OFFER YOU
A SERIES PICK-UP, NO PILOT?

14:57.959 --> 14:58.875
YES.

14:58.875 --> 15:00.709
You've got to tell me
these things.

15:00.709 --> 15:02.208
KIM SALLY HEARD ABOUT IT.

15:02.208 --> 15:05.542
SHE'S WILLING TO MATCH IT
AND KICK IN A BIG PENALTY.

15:05.542 --> 15:06.875
WHAT?

15:06.875 --> 15:07.792
IT'S EILEEN.

15:07.792 --> 15:09.041
FOX IS WILLING TO OFFER US

15:09.041 --> 15:10.875
A SERIES PICK-UP
WITH A BIG PENALTY.

15:10.875 --> 15:13.041
THE PENALTY BEING
WE WOULD HAVE TO DO IT.

15:13.041 --> 15:14.792
EILEEN, I'M SORRY.

15:14.792 --> 15:17.125
WE SAID NO TO CAROL,
AND IT'S NO TO KIM.

15:17.125 --> 15:18.375
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

15:20.083 --> 15:22.125
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
[ SIGHS ] UNBELIEVABLE.

15:23.834 --> 15:25.500
HELLO.

15:25.500 --> 15:26.500
HI, SWEETIE.

15:26.500 --> 15:28.417
HI. I'M OUT TO DINNER.
CAN I CALL YOU BACK?

15:28.417 --> 15:29.959
NO.
NO?

15:29.959 --> 15:32.041
ELLIOT SALAD
READ YOUR SCRIPT.

15:32.041 --> 15:34.250
HE REALLY LIKED IT.

15:34.250 --> 15:37.333
HE SAID IT WAS THE ONE
SANE THING CASTOR SAID.

15:37.333 --> 15:40.583
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE EVEN
HAVING THIS CONVERSATION AGAIN.

15:40.583 --> 15:42.000
IT'S ELLIOT SALAD!

15:42.000 --> 15:44.917
How do I say no
to Elliot Salad?

15:44.917 --> 15:48.250
I DON'T CARE.
WITH CROUTONS, BUT SAY IT.

15:48.250 --> 15:49.250
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

15:49.250 --> 15:50.417
WHAT'S...

15:50.417 --> 15:51.542
ELLIOT SALAD
READ THE SCRIPT,

15:51.542 --> 15:53.417
AND NOW HE WANTS TO DO IT.

15:53.417 --> 15:54.458
SHE SAID --
I heard.

15:54.458 --> 15:55.709
PUT BEV ON.

15:55.709 --> 15:57.166
SHE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.
SWITCH.

15:57.166 --> 15:58.208
[ SIGHS ]
SERIOUSLY?

15:59.208 --> 16:01.250
BEV, HI.

16:01.250 --> 16:04.333
WE HAVEN'T REALLY GOTTEN TO KNOW
EACH OTHER THAT WELL...

16:04.333 --> 16:05.333
OR AT ALL.

16:05.333 --> 16:06.625
Okay, sure.

16:06.625 --> 16:09.625
BUT CAN I JUST SAY,
AS YOUR AGENT --

16:09.625 --> 16:12.000
OUR AGENT?
SHE'S OUR AGENT?
KIND OF.

16:12.000 --> 16:13.834
WHAT ABOUT STANLEY?
HE'S OKAY WITH IT.

16:13.834 --> 16:15.458
IT'S LIKE WAKING UP
FROM A COMA.

16:15.458 --> 16:16.959
Bev, listen to me.

16:16.959 --> 16:19.875
YOU'VE GOT TWO NETWORKS
COMPETING FOR YOU.

16:19.875 --> 16:21.125
IT'S A BIG DEAL.

16:21.125 --> 16:22.125
NOT TO ME.

16:22.125 --> 16:23.500
PUT HER BACK ON.
SWITCH.

16:23.500 --> 16:25.041
JESUS CHRIST.

16:25.041 --> 16:26.417
JUST PUT ME ON SPEAKER.

16:26.417 --> 16:28.375
YOU'RE ON SPEAKER.
All right.

16:28.375 --> 16:30.875
WHAT WILL IT TAKE
TO GET YOU TO STAY HERE?

16:30.875 --> 16:33.583
Name it.
I will make it happen.

16:33.583 --> 16:34.625
YOU WANT SOMEONE

16:34.625 --> 16:37.625
TO BRING YOU TEA AND CRUMPETS
EVERY AFTERNOON?

16:37.625 --> 16:39.375
I WILL DO IT PERSONALLY.

16:39.375 --> 16:41.041
YOU -- YOU NEED MORE RAIN?

16:41.041 --> 16:42.750
WE GOT MACHINES FOR THAT.

16:42.750 --> 16:44.667
What do you want?

16:44.667 --> 16:45.750
JUDI DENCH?

16:45.750 --> 16:48.583
THERE ARE WAYS TO GET HER HERE.

16:48.583 --> 16:49.709
WHAT'S SHE OFFERING YOU?

16:49.709 --> 16:51.500
JUDI DENCH, APPARENTLY.

16:51.500 --> 16:52.667
FOR WHICH PART?

16:52.667 --> 16:54.667
I THINK IN GENERAL.

16:54.667 --> 16:56.458
ALL RIGHT.
PUT ME ON SPEAKER, TOO.

16:56.458 --> 16:58.417
[ SIGHS ]

16:58.417 --> 17:01.500
Carol, hi.
It's Eileen.

17:01.500 --> 17:02.792
CAROL: Hi, sweetie.

17:02.792 --> 17:05.583
Kim is prepared to match
whatever you're offering,

17:05.583 --> 17:06.667
and you know Kim.

17:06.667 --> 17:08.000
Yeah, I know Kim.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.500
She was my assistant
for four years.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.291
I don't care
what Kim wants.

17:12.291 --> 17:15.834
Elliot wants this to happen,
so it is going to happen.

17:15.834 --> 17:18.208
NO, IT'S NOT
GOING TO HAPPEN.

17:18.208 --> 17:19.417
THEN HANG UP.

17:19.417 --> 17:21.125
JUST HANG UP.
HANG THE FUCK UP.

17:21.125 --> 17:22.333
WE'RE HANGING UP.

17:22.333 --> 17:23.625
Don't hang up.
Don't hang up!
Don't hang up.

17:23.625 --> 17:24.625
BYE.
Don't hang up!

17:24.625 --> 17:25.875
NOW TURN THEM OFF.

17:25.875 --> 17:27.458
ENOUGH WITH THE FUCKING PHONES.

17:27.458 --> 17:29.667
STARTING NOW,
IT'S A NO-PHONE DINNER, YES?

17:29.667 --> 17:30.709
AGREED.
DONE.

17:30.709 --> 17:33.667
[ CELLPHONE RINGTONE PLAYS ]
HANG ON A SEC.

17:33.667 --> 17:34.834
WHAT'S UP?

17:34.834 --> 17:37.041
YOU SITTING DOWN?
YEAH.

17:37.041 --> 17:38.333
THEY BLINKED AGAIN.

17:38.333 --> 17:40.000
WHO BLINKED?
NBC.

17:40.000 --> 17:40.959
MEANING?

17:40.959 --> 17:42.542
YOU GOT THE SHOW.

17:42.542 --> 17:45.166
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

17:48.041 --> 17:51.375
GOT TO SAY, I AM NOT
GOING TO MISS THIS PLACE.

17:51.375 --> 17:52.375
OH, I KNOW.

17:52.375 --> 17:54.959
OF ALL THE ROOMS
WE'VE EVER BEEN IN,

17:54.959 --> 17:57.083
THIS MAY BE
MY LEAST FAVORITE.

17:57.083 --> 17:59.583
AND WE'VE BEEN
IN ANNE FRANK'S HOUSE.

17:59.583 --> 18:00.542
[ LAUGHS ]

18:00.542 --> 18:04.166
[ TYPEWRITER CLICKING,
BELL CHIMES ]

18:04.166 --> 18:05.917
Merc: [ LAUGHS ]

18:05.917 --> 18:07.792
[ Cockney accent ]
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

18:07.792 --> 18:08.625
IT'S FISH AND CHIPS.

18:08.625 --> 18:10.709
BLOODY HELL.
FUCK ME.

18:10.709 --> 18:12.291
COME HERE, YOU.

18:12.291 --> 18:13.458
REALLY? STILL?

18:13.458 --> 18:14.709
COME HERE.

18:14.709 --> 18:16.250
[ LAUGHS ]

18:16.250 --> 18:18.125
[ Normal voice ] AH!

18:18.125 --> 18:20.083
AH, YOU KNOW,
THIS IS SO WEIRD.

18:20.083 --> 18:22.959
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT YOU TWO.
WHY?

18:22.959 --> 18:24.542
WE GOT TO MAKE
SOME MORE TV TOGETHER.

18:24.542 --> 18:26.500
[ Laughing ]
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

18:26.500 --> 18:28.208
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS --

18:28.208 --> 18:30.125
YOU NEED SOMEONE LIKE ME
TO RUN INTERFERENCE,

18:30.125 --> 18:31.917
KEEP THE IDIOTS
OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

18:31.917 --> 18:34.375
THIS MAY BE
MY FAVORITE MOMENT SO FAR.

18:34.375 --> 18:36.583
I'M TELLING YOU --
SOMEONE'S GOT TO PROTECT YOU

18:36.583 --> 18:38.291
FROM THOSE ASSHOLES
AT THE NETWORK.

18:38.291 --> 18:39.792
WHERE WERE YOU
WHEN WE MET YOU?

18:39.792 --> 18:41.917
[ LAUGHS ]

18:41.917 --> 18:43.083
UNFORTUNATELY,

18:43.083 --> 18:45.125
WE'RE HEADING BACK TO LONDON
TOMORROW.

18:45.125 --> 18:46.625
WELL,
WHAT ABOUT "PUCKS"?

18:46.625 --> 18:47.667
OVER.

18:47.667 --> 18:50.458
NO! I LOVED THAT SHOW.

18:50.458 --> 18:51.959
DID YOU?

18:51.959 --> 18:55.333
WELL, AT LEAST THAT COCKSUCKER
LeBLANC'S OUT OF A JOB.

18:55.333 --> 18:56.834
THAT'S ONE GOOD THING.

18:56.834 --> 18:58.208
ACTUALLY,
SORRY TO DISAPPOINT YOU,

18:58.208 --> 18:59.959
BUT HE'S STARRING
IN A BIG NBC PILOT.

18:59.959 --> 19:01.667
REALLY?

19:01.667 --> 19:02.792
MM, SOME DRAMA.

19:02.792 --> 19:03.917
SUPPOSED TO BE
THEIR HOT NEW THING.

19:03.917 --> 19:05.667
OH.

19:05.667 --> 19:08.750
GOOD FOR HIM.

19:13.834 --> 19:16.125
ALL RIGHT, KITCHEN'S DONE.
WHAT NEXT?

19:16.125 --> 19:18.291
ELECTRIC TOOTHBRUSH
WITH AMERICAN PLUG?

19:18.291 --> 19:19.959
CHUCK IT.
CONSIDER IT CHUCKED.

19:19.959 --> 19:21.709
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]
OH, GOD.

19:21.709 --> 19:23.166
THE CAR'S HERE ALREADY?

19:27.375 --> 19:29.333
HI.

19:29.333 --> 19:30.792
I CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.

19:30.792 --> 19:32.667
AND...

19:32.667 --> 19:34.333
AND NOTHING.

19:34.333 --> 19:38.000
I JUST WANTED TO GIVE YOU A HUG
BEFORE YOU GO.

19:38.000 --> 19:39.166
I'M SAD.

19:42.500 --> 19:44.667
I KNOW.

19:44.667 --> 19:47.417
I'M GONNA MISS YOU
SO MUCH.

19:47.417 --> 19:49.500
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, TOO.

19:49.500 --> 19:50.834
I REALLY AM.

19:50.834 --> 19:52.417
SUSAN SARANDON
READ YOUR SCRIPT.

19:52.417 --> 19:53.834
WHAT?
WHAT?

19:53.834 --> 19:56.667
OH, GOD. I WASN'T GONNA SAY IT.
IT JUST POPPED OUT.

19:56.667 --> 19:58.208
LET GO OF ME.

19:58.208 --> 19:59.417
DON'T BE MAD.

19:59.417 --> 20:02.667
SHE READ IT
AND REALLY WANTS TO DO IT.

20:02.667 --> 20:05.709
SUSAN SARANDON.
I LOVE SUSAN SARANDON.

20:05.709 --> 20:07.083
AND SHE LOVES THE PART.

20:07.083 --> 20:09.000
SHE'S NEVER DONE A SERIES.

20:09.000 --> 20:11.875
SHE SAID THIS IS WHAT
SHE'S BEEN WAITING FOR.

20:11.875 --> 20:14.542
COME ON.
SUSAN SARANDON.

20:14.542 --> 20:16.291
OH, PLEASE!

20:16.291 --> 20:18.583
YOU KNOW BY THE TIME
THEY'RE DONE WITH US,

20:18.583 --> 20:20.542
IT'S NOT GOING TO BE
SUSAN SARANDON.

20:20.542 --> 20:22.750
SHE'S JUST SAYING
SUSAN SARANDON TODAY.

20:22.750 --> 20:24.750
OOH, LOOK -- A CARROT.

20:24.750 --> 20:27.917
BUT ONCE WE'RE IN,
IT'S, "OH, SORRY.

20:27.917 --> 20:31.625
"SUSAN CAN'T DO IT.
BUT YOU KNOW WHO WE CAN GET?

20:31.625 --> 20:33.542
"SOMEONE SHITTY

20:33.542 --> 20:34.792
WHO'S TOTALLY WRONG
FOR THE PART."

20:34.792 --> 20:38.542
YOU WATCH --
IT'LL END UP BEING...

20:38.542 --> 20:39.709
THIS CUP.

20:39.709 --> 20:42.291
SHE'LL RING US UP ONE DAY.
[ Nasally ] "HOLD FOR CAROL."

20:42.291 --> 20:44.375
AND SHE'LL BE ALL...
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

20:44.375 --> 20:47.041
[ As Carol ]
"YOU GUYS, GUESS WHAT --

20:47.041 --> 20:50.000
"THE CUP WANTS TO DO YOUR SHOW.
THIS IS HUGE.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.500
THE CUP
TURNS DOWN EVERYTHING!"

20:52.500 --> 20:54.917
[ Normal voice ]
AND WE'LL BE, "UH, THE CUP?"

20:54.917 --> 20:57.000
AND SHE'LL SAY,
[As Carol] "SERIOUSLY?

20:57.000 --> 20:58.583
"YOU DON'T KNOW THE CUP?

20:58.583 --> 21:02.250
FROM 'WHERE'S MY SAUCER?'
AND 'ME AND THE SPOON.'"

21:02.250 --> 21:05.417
[ Normal voice ]
YEAH, AND SUDDENLY,
WE'LL BE DOING A SHOW

21:05.417 --> 21:07.000
STARRING A FUCKING CUP,

21:07.000 --> 21:08.250
WHO YOU JUST KNOW

21:08.250 --> 21:11.250
IS GONNA WANT TO MAKE
LOTS OF VERY CUPPY CHANGES

21:11.250 --> 21:14.542
BECAUSE IT NEEDS
TO MAKE IT ITS OWN.

21:14.542 --> 21:16.417
[ SIGHS ]

21:18.125 --> 21:19.375
DID SUSAN SAY
WHAT SHE LIKED ABOUT IT?

21:19.375 --> 21:20.792
OH!
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:20.792 --> 21:22.542
[ CUP THUMPS ]

21:23.667 --> 21:25.458
HEY.
CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.

21:25.458 --> 21:26.542
AND THAT'S ALL?

21:26.542 --> 21:28.083
UH, YEAH.

21:30.166 --> 21:31.625
YOU SEE?

21:31.625 --> 21:32.667
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

21:32.667 --> 21:34.417
THIS IS WHAT SAYING GOODBYE
LOOKS LIKE.

21:34.417 --> 21:36.750
IT'S JUST SAYING GOODBYE --

21:36.750 --> 21:39.333
NO HIDDEN AGENDAS,
NO LAST-DITCH EFFORTS.

21:39.333 --> 21:41.417
SUSAN SARANDON
WANTS TO DO OUR SHOW!

21:41.417 --> 21:42.333
"PUCKS"?

21:42.333 --> 21:43.333
NO, THAT OTHER SCRIPT.

21:43.333 --> 21:44.709
OOH.
I WORKED WITH HER.

21:44.709 --> 21:45.917
SHE'S AMAZING.

21:45.917 --> 21:46.959
IF YOU COULD GET
SUSAN SARANDON...

21:46.959 --> 21:49.250
WE'VE GOT HER.

21:50.250 --> 21:51.709
PROBABLY GOOD
YOU'RE GOING HOME.

21:51.709 --> 21:52.917
[ SIGHS ]
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:52.917 --> 21:55.125
[ CUP THUDS ]
SHIT. THAT'S THE CAR.

21:55.125 --> 21:57.083
WHAT ARE WE FORGETTING?

21:57.083 --> 21:58.250
OH, GOOD.

21:58.250 --> 22:00.417
I'M SO GLAD I CAUGHT YOU
BEFORE YOU LEFT.

22:00.417 --> 22:02.709
Eileen: HI, GUYS.

22:02.709 --> 22:04.125
I'VE GOT BIG NEWS.

22:04.125 --> 22:06.166
CBS WANTS IN.

22:06.166 --> 22:08.125
THAT'S THREE NETWORKS.

22:08.125 --> 22:10.458
WELL,
ONLY ONE IS GETTING IT.

22:10.458 --> 22:13.166
CBS IS GUARANTEEING THEM
A KILLER TIME SLOT.

22:13.166 --> 22:15.875
YOU DON'T HAVE
A KILLER TIME SLOT.

22:15.875 --> 22:16.959
THAT'S WORTH A LOT.

22:16.959 --> 22:19.208
I GOT THEM
SUSAN SARANDON.

22:19.208 --> 22:20.375
[ LAUGHS ]

22:20.375 --> 22:22.083
SUSAN SARANDON'S
NOT DOING TELEVISION.

22:22.083 --> 22:23.125
THANK YOU.
MNH-MNH.

22:23.125 --> 22:25.000
SHE'S GOT THREE MOVIES
LINED UP.

22:25.000 --> 22:28.000
WHAT ABOUT GOLDIE HAWN?

22:28.000 --> 22:30.250
OOH!
SHE'S GREAT.

22:30.250 --> 22:31.333
SHE'S A CLIENT.

22:31.333 --> 22:33.125
STOP CASTING.

22:33.125 --> 22:34.375
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
MM.

22:34.375 --> 22:35.500
[ SIGHS ]

22:35.500 --> 22:36.959
KIM SALLY FROM FOX.

22:36.959 --> 22:38.208
HI, HONEY.

22:38.208 --> 22:40.500
I'M ACTUALLY
WITH THEM NOW.

22:40.500 --> 22:41.583
NOT WITH ME.

22:41.583 --> 22:44.041
I'VE ALSO GOT
CAROL RANCE HERE.

22:44.041 --> 22:45.166
KIM WANTS
TO COME OVER, TOO.

22:45.166 --> 22:46.375
Beverly: NO!

22:46.375 --> 22:47.500
THIS IS FUN.

22:47.500 --> 22:48.583
DON'T WORRY.

22:48.583 --> 22:49.834
I'LL CALL BACK
IF ANYTHING CHANGES.

22:49.834 --> 22:52.000
NOTHING
IS GOING TO CHANGE.

22:52.000 --> 22:53.709
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

23:03.250 --> 23:05.166
AREN'T YOU GOING
TO GET THAT?

23:05.166 --> 23:07.750
WE NEVER USE THAT PHONE.
IT CAME WITH THE HOUSE.

23:07.750 --> 23:09.917
IT'S NEVER RUNG
THE WHOLE TIME WE'VE BEEN HERE.

23:09.917 --> 23:11.417
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
THE NUMBER.

23:14.000 --> 23:16.667
I'M SORRY.
I CAN NOT NOT ANSWER A PHONE.

23:19.709 --> 23:21.291
[ BEEPS ]
HELLO.

23:21.291 --> 23:23.000
MAN: Hi.
I'm calling from CBS.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.083
I have Les Moonves
for Sean and Beverly.

23:25.083 --> 23:29.500
UH, SEAN AND BEVERLY
ARE RIGHT HERE.

23:29.500 --> 23:31.542
You're on with Les.

23:31.542 --> 23:34.000
HI. IS THIS SEAN AND BEVERLY?

23:34.000 --> 23:35.583
UH, IT'S LES MOON--

23:35.583 --> 23:37.166
[ ALL GASP ]

23:37.166 --> 23:38.291
WE HAVE A PLANE TO CATCH.

23:38.291 --> 23:39.500
ARE YOU CRAZY?

23:39.500 --> 23:40.917
I'LL CALL HIM BACK
AND SAY WE WERE DISCONNECTED.

23:40.917 --> 23:42.875
YOU HUNG UP ON LES MOONVES?
I'M CALLING SUSAN SARANDON.

23:42.875 --> 23:43.959
TELL HER I SAID HELLO.

23:43.959 --> 23:46.250
HOW CAN WE LEAVE?
EVERYBODY WANTS US.

23:46.250 --> 23:48.417
WHICH IS WHY
WE SHOULD LEAVE.

23:48.417 --> 23:49.875
IT'S THE PERFECT TIME.
Eileen: THERE WAS A PROBLEM
WITH THE PHONE.

23:49.875 --> 23:51.917
I DON'T KNOW -- MAYBE
THE ELECTRICITY WENT OUT.
WHAT?

23:51.917 --> 23:55.542
WE HAVE SPENT A YEAR
FEELING ABSOLUTELY POWERLESS.

23:55.542 --> 23:57.500
AS SOON AS WE SAY YES
TO ONE OF THOSE FUCKERS,

23:57.500 --> 23:58.625
WE'RE RIGHT BACK THERE,

23:58.625 --> 24:02.250
BUT IF WE GO NOW, WITH ALL
OF THEM FIGHTING OVER US,

24:02.250 --> 24:06.417
THAT'S AS GOOD AS IT GETS
IN THIS TOWN.

24:06.417 --> 24:08.917
THIS IS THE GIRAFFE.

24:08.917 --> 24:11.500
UH-HUH.

24:11.500 --> 24:15.959
HEY, YOUR CAR'S HERE.
WHAT SHOULD I TELL HIM?

24:15.959 --> 24:18.875
...CALL HERE. RIGHT.

24:18.875 --> 24:20.583
WE'RE LEAVING.

24:21.875 --> 24:22.959
OH!

24:22.959 --> 24:24.625
REALLY?

24:24.625 --> 24:27.208
SHOULD WE, UH...

24:27.208 --> 24:28.625
GET LES MOONVES BACK
ON THE PHONE BECAUSE IT WAS...

24:28.625 --> 24:29.667
NO, YOU'RE NOT --
I DON'T WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

24:29.667 --> 24:30.959
...IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.
I WANT TO TALK TO SUSAN.

24:30.959 --> 24:32.250
FUCK 'EM.

24:32.250 --> 24:33.709
[ LAUGHS ]

24:33.709 --> 24:36.250
GET OUT OF HERE.

24:52.959 --> 24:55.500
MR. SALAD!

24:55.500 --> 24:57.291
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE IN TOWN.

24:57.291 --> 24:59.125
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:59.125 --> 25:02.000
SO I'M STILL GETTING HUGS?

25:02.000 --> 25:02.917
WHY NOT?

25:02.917 --> 25:04.917
AS I RECALL,
LAST TIME WE SPOKE,

25:04.917 --> 25:07.000
YOU TOLD ME
I COULD GO FUCK MYSELF

25:07.000 --> 25:08.417
WITH CASTOR SOTTO'S DICK.

25:08.417 --> 25:10.208
AH, YOU FIRED ME.
I WAS A LITTLE HURT.

25:10.208 --> 25:11.917
WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

25:11.917 --> 25:13.125
ANYWAY, UH, BE WELL.

25:13.125 --> 25:14.291
OH!

25:14.291 --> 25:15.458
I HEARD ABOUT MATT LeBLANC

25:15.458 --> 25:17.500
GETTING THAT BIG PILOT
OVER AT NBC.

25:17.500 --> 25:18.917
WHAT?

25:18.917 --> 25:20.041
WHAT?
YOU DIDN'T KNOW?

25:20.041 --> 25:22.125
SUPPOSEDLY, THEY'RE BUILDING
A WHOLE NIGHT AROUND IT.

25:22.125 --> 25:23.667
ARE YOU KIDDING?
I GOT TO SAY --

25:23.667 --> 25:25.208
I WAS KIND OF SURPRISED
YOU'D LET THAT HAPPEN.

25:25.208 --> 25:28.041
I MEAN, NOT MY BUSINESS ANYMORE,
BUT HOW'S THAT LOOK?

25:28.041 --> 25:29.583
HE BOMBS WITH YOU GUYS,

25:29.583 --> 25:32.125
THEN GETS A BIG HIT
ACROSS THE STREET?

25:32.125 --> 25:34.333
PEOPLE GET FIRED FOR THAT.

25:34.333 --> 25:36.500
AND IT'S NBC?

25:36.500 --> 25:37.792
MM-HMM.

25:37.792 --> 25:39.083
JESUS.

25:39.083 --> 25:40.542
AH! SORRY I EVEN
MENTIONED IT.

25:47.875 --> 25:49.625
ELLIOT, HI.

25:49.625 --> 25:52.041
HAVE WE OFFICIALLY CANCELED
"PUCKS"?

25:52.041 --> 25:53.709
UH, NO.

25:53.709 --> 25:55.125
YOU SURE?

25:55.125 --> 25:57.125
THE PAPERWORK'S STILL HERE
ON MY DESK.

25:57.125 --> 26:00.250
PICK IT UP FOR SIX MORE.

26:00.250 --> 26:01.792
WAIT.

26:01.792 --> 26:04.875
YOU WANT
TO PICK UP "PUCKS"?

26:04.875 --> 26:06.083
TODAY.

26:06.083 --> 26:09.083
BUT...YOU HATE "PUCKS."

26:09.083 --> 26:11.333
I HATE NBC MORE.

26:15.208 --> 26:17.125
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:17.125 --> 26:19.709
MONSIEUR LeBLANC!

26:19.709 --> 26:21.208
HEY!

26:21.208 --> 26:22.667
[ BOTH CHUCKLING ]

26:22.667 --> 26:26.000
HOW EXCITING.
OUR LITTLE ADVENTURE BEGINS.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.083
I KNOW.

26:27.083 --> 26:28.208
VERY COOL.

26:28.208 --> 26:30.834
YOU ARE GOING TO BE
SO WONDERFUL IN THIS.

26:30.834 --> 26:33.083
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
I CAN ALREADY SMELL YOUR EMMY.

26:33.083 --> 26:35.542
[ SNIFFING ]
NO, THAT WAS ME.

26:35.542 --> 26:36.917
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:36.917 --> 26:39.208
[ CELLPHONE RINGTONE PLAYS ]

26:39.208 --> 26:42.417
UGH.
HANG ON A SECOND -- AGENT.

26:42.417 --> 26:45.208
HEY, UH,
CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

26:45.208 --> 26:47.542
YEAH, I'M ALREADY HERE.

26:52.250 --> 26:54.750
ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING ME?

26:54.750 --> 26:57.583
THEY CAN'T DO THAT.
WE WERE CANCELED.

26:57.583 --> 27:00.250
WHAT DOES "NOT OFFICIALLY" MEAN?

27:00.250 --> 27:03.750
THAT'S BULLSHIT.

27:03.750 --> 27:07.333
OKAY, SO WHAT DOES THAT MEAN
ABOUT THIS?

27:07.333 --> 27:12.083
I DON'T CARE. I'M DOING IT.
THEY CAN'T STOP ME.

27:12.083 --> 27:13.500
OH.

27:21.291 --> 27:23.333
Beverly:
HOW WONDERFUL IS THIS?

27:23.333 --> 27:25.333
IT'S WET!

27:25.333 --> 27:26.834
REMEMBER WET?

27:26.834 --> 27:30.583
MM, AND SLIPPERY, TOO.

27:30.583 --> 27:34.458
I'VE MISSED
EVERY PRECARIOUS INCH OF IT.

27:34.458 --> 27:35.709
HARD TO BELIEVE THAT,
YESTERDAY,

27:35.709 --> 27:37.458
WE WERE SITTING IN TRAFFIC
ON THE 405.

27:37.458 --> 27:38.792
MM.

27:38.792 --> 27:42.250
OH, IT'S LIKE WAKING UP
FROM SOME FEVER DREAM.

27:42.250 --> 27:45.417
WE'RE AWAKE, AND WE'RE HERE.

27:45.417 --> 27:47.834
AND I LOVE YOU.

27:47.834 --> 27:50.125
LOVE YOU, TOO.

27:50.125 --> 27:51.667
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:55.875 --> 27:59.458
MM. [ CHUCKLES ]
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

28:01.333 --> 28:03.500
IT'S AN L.A. NUMBER.

28:03.500 --> 28:05.583
DON'T ANSWER IT.

28:05.583 --> 28:10.333
OH, DEAR GOD,
DON'T ANSWER IT.

28:10.333 --> 28:12.166
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]
